During a meeting with South Korean President Moon Jae-in, President Trump discussed the progress being made in their relationship, particularly in terms of trade and working together on the issue of North Korea. President Moon expressed his appreciation for the United States' firm response to North Korean provocations and believed that their coordination was strong. President Trump also mentioned his intention to address the trade deal between the two countries, but emphasized that their focus would primarily be on the military and their excellent relationship. The meeting took place before a tri-meeting with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe.